HEADWORD: Fratery
<hw>Fra"ter*y</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frater</ets> brother: cf. It. <ets>frateria</ets> a brotherhood of
monks. See <er>Friar</er>.]</ety> <def>A frater house. See under
<er>Frater</er>.</def></p>

<p><-- Frat house. Short for fraternity house, a building owned by a
college fraternity in which members may live. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fratrage</ent>⟦br⟧
